'North Rhine-Westphalia' ( ) is the most populous state of Germany, with four of
the country's ten largest cities. The state was formed in 1946 as a merger of
the northern Rhineland and Westphalia, both formerly parts of Prussia. Its
capital is DÃ¼sseldorf; the biggest city is Cologne. The state is currently run
by a coalition of the Social Democrats and Greens.
